{"TopicId":185819,"ForumId":66,"TopicTitle":"KSP Loading... Preview: Grip Pads","CreatedByName":"St4rdust","CreatedById":196576,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-25T14:55:26Z","PageNum":3,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T17:42:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625681\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561570226\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Majorjim! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLOL, what robotic grabbers?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnes that people build.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat walkers are you on about?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T19:32:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625561\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561553422\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Majorjim! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0I\u0027m just curious as to why squad chose to release all these different shape parts for what is clearly a single Issue, the slippery walkers.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s a bit like asking why their are different size and shape wing parts for something that has a single use: to generate lift.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the use will go much further than that just walkers anyway, (which are fast becoming a big thing). KSP folk are very good at finding out of the box uses for parts.\u00A0\u00A0I also reckon the long rectangular ones will be adopted for tank treads rather quickly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fulgur","CreatedById":195204,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T20:50:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the one hand, rovers are about 20x quicker than walkers. On the other hand, walkers will be much quicker with improved friction. On the third hand, walkers are\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ekerbal.\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T21:09:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWalkers are\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ecool.\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRobotic frogs are even cooler though. Right \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181256-klapaucius/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022181256\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181256-klapaucius/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Klapaucius\u003C/a\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Klapaucius/Aristophanes-the-Frog\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Klapaucius/Aristophanes-the-Frog\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jimmidii","CreatedById":9293,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-26T23:06:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625552\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561551942\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160254\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Maxsimal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Maxsimal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey were considered for both uses, as you\u0027ll see when you get to read the part descriptions. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow that I think about it, this would definitely make claw grabbers more feasible...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr extending feet to stabilise a crane...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr clamps that can hold a payload in a cargo bay, release it, and then secure it again...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmmm...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk, now I\u0027m starting to get ideas \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shadowmage","CreatedById":138730,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-27T00:30:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQ:\u00A0 Did you fix the fact that \u0026gt; half of the objects in the game don\u0027t have physics materials applied?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(I had tried to fix this problem, and other similar issues, but the lack of physics materials on most terrain objects made it into a giant painful hack)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lajoswinkler","CreatedById":79159,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-28T00:16:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m having difficulties with understanding the purpose of these. If we want more stability, why not making already existing stuff more stable? Can anyone explain?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-28T00:43:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223626309\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561681012\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002279159\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lajoswinkler\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, lajoswinkler said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m having difficulties with understanding the purpose of these. If we want more stability, why not making already existing stuff more stable? Can anyone explain?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour logic isn\u0027t wanted here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-28T01:11:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223626309\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561681012\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002279159\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lajoswinkler\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n55 minutes ago, lajoswinkler said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m having difficulties with understanding the purpose of these. If we want more stability, why not making already existing stuff more stable? Can anyone explain?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey allow you to add traction to legs. For example, with the new robotic parts, folks are starting to build walkers. If you look at video of these machines, you will noticed they all slip a lot. It was suggested that something akin to a tread or sole of shoe would be good to use for these feet to give them traction. Currently, the only parts with that kind of traction control are wheels, which cannot be easily adapted for this purpose.\u00A0 Check out the entries in Walker Challenge to see better what I am talking about.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022153808\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4924255512\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/184892-breaking-ground-walker-speed-challenge/\u0026amp;tab=comments\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3608398\u0026amp;embedComment=3608398\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-3608398\u0022 style=\u0022height:295px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSecondly, this would also allow for base building on uneven terrain.\u00A0 Currently just about anything that is not sitting on wheels will slide downhill.\u00A0Creators can (I assume) set\u00A0 a high friction rate for the feet of their base, thus allowing them to move off the plains on to sloped terrain.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFinally, it seems Squad have also taken that to mean we can in future employ them to make gripping items as well so we can create robotic clamps to lift items.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe reason to have these as a separate part, is you don\u0027t always want traction. I imagine as well that applying this to all parts would be a big undertaking.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-06-28T01:13:16Z\u0022 title=\u002206/28/2019 01:13  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJune 28, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Klapaucius\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wallygator","CreatedById":97357,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-28T03:07:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223625207\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561495036\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163018\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nestor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/25/2019 at 10:37 PM, nestor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey are new parts that you\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E can place for e\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Extra friction.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmmm... was going to respond with some snappy comment and then realised...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\non a serious note... is this a \u201Ccomb over\u201D to a deeper unfixable issue in unity?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-28T11:11:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223626381\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561691272\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297357\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wallygator\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Wallygator said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmmm... was going to respond with some snappy comment and then realised...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\non a serious note... is this a \u201Ccomb over\u201D to a deeper unfixable issue in unity?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf these parts fix it, it\u0027s not really unfixable.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerbMav","CreatedById":70338,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-28T15:17:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223626309\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561681012\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002279159\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lajoswinkler\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, lajoswinkler said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0If we want more stability, why not making already existing stuff more stable?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo refine this question:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile we might need more grip(pish parts as foundations) for a base, does anything speak against giving landing legs more grip themselves?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-28T15:51:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223626621\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561735056\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270338\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KerbMav\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n33 minutes ago, KerbMav said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile we might need more grip(pish parts as foundations) for a base, does anything speak against giving landing legs more grip themselves?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u201CHa! That\u2019s what they \u003Ci\u003Eexpect\u003C/i\u003E\u00A0us to do!\u201D\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidCosmos","CreatedById":192336,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-28T15:53:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan\u0027t wait to play with these things!!!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wallygator","CreatedById":97357,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-28T16:18:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223626520\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561720276\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105132\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022klgraham1013\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, klgraham1013 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf these parts fix it, it\u0027s not really unfixable.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs long as they can be\u00A0attached\u00A0to anything then I tend to agree.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nwillard","CreatedById":197319,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-29T02:00:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSoooooooo... update ETA?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"goldenpeach","CreatedById":34566,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-29T03:40:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forums \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/197319-nwillard/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022197319\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/197319-nwillard/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@nwillard\u003C/a\u003E!\u003Cbr\u003E\nUnfortunately, Squad doesn\u2019t announce update release dates so your question is likely to remain unanswered.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Serenity","CreatedById":179192,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-29T07:32:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am gonna try picking up a module and see if i can move it around.Would be nice to avoid the whole docking/undocking part.What do you think? Will it actually work?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomething like this\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022bru02252-0.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002254.57\u0022 height=\u0022558\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022http://cdn.ecommercedns.uk/files/8/228498/1/5190971/bru02252-0.jpg\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-06-29T07:33:01Z\u0022 title=\u002206/29/2019 07:33  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJune 29, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Boyster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-29T12:15:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223626321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561682626\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105132\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022klgraham1013\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/28/2019 at 12:43 PM, klgraham1013 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour logic isn\u0027t wanted here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure what this comment is about. The poster asked a legitimate question.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-29T13:10:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223627058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561810544\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181256\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Klapaucius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n52 minutes ago, Klapaucius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure what this comment is about. The poster asked a legitimate question.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe\u0027s agreeing with the idea behind the question.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-29T13:58:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223627058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561810544\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181256\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Klapaucius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Klapaucius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure what this comment is about. The poster asked a legitimate question.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe comment is sarcasm.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Enceos","CreatedById":110725,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-29T20:38:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223626309\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561681012\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002279159\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lajoswinkler\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/27/2019 at 6:16 PM, lajoswinkler said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m having difficulties with understanding the purpose of these. If we want more stability, why not making already existing stuff more stable? Can anyone explain?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll the colliders in the game are smooth like a mirror, that\u0027s why they slide against each other so well.\u00A0The new parts are covered in digital glue which adds maximum friction locally. I believe devs can\u0027t just bump up the global friction because 1: imitating spikes on boots requires more than average friction, 2:\u00A0because it will affect current wheel colliders.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lajoswinkler","CreatedById":79159,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-29T20:58:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223627218\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561840683\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Enceos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, Enceos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll the colliders in the game are smooth like a mirror, that\u0027s why they slide against each other so well.\u00A0The new parts are covered in digital glue which adds maximum friction locally. I believe devs can\u0027t just bump up the global friction because 1: imitating spikes on boots requires more than average friction, 2:\u00A0because it will affect current wheel colliders.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s it. I\u0027m making a custom built wheel now.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jognt","CreatedById":176871,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-29T22:43:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt looks nice. But I have to admit I\u2019m skeptical about whether or not it will play nice. Anything new at this point sounds like \u2018another thing I\u2019ll need to fix myself/with a mod\u2019.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease.. give me a good reason to believe in you guys again. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EEdit: there are several mentions of people being excited about using these for landing legs/bases, yet on the first page there\u2019s already a post that says these aren\u2019t going to help (much) with that.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003EIs this really just another disappointment waiting to be released?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-06-29T22:47:16Z\u0022 title=\u002206/29/2019 10:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJune 29, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Jognt\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sh1pman","CreatedById":147869,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-06-29T23:22:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223627257\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022185819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221561848206\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176871\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jognt\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, Jognt said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EEdit\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E: there are several mentions of people being excited about using these for landing legs/bases, yet on the first page there\u2019s already a post that says these aren\u2019t going to help (much) with that.\u00A0\u003C/span\u003EIs this really just another disappointment waiting to be released?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWouldn\u2019t it be great if there was a way to nail bases/landers to the ground?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}